    {
      "question": "For a given distribution, if Mean = 20 and Mode = 20, find the Median using the empirical relationship.",
      "answer": "(C)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Use the empirical formula: Mode = 3(Median) - 2(Mean).",
          "Substitute the given values: 20 = 3(Median) - 2(20).",
          "20 = 3(Median) - 40 => 60 = 3(Median) => Median = 20."
        ],
        "derivation": "20 = 3(\\text{Median}) - 2(20) \\implies 20 + 40 = 3(\\text{Median}) \\implies \\text{Median} = 60/3 = 20"
      },
